    ],
    "methodology": "Interpreter complaint and no-show data from MOJ quarterly court interpreting statistics. NRPSI membership figures from their published annual reports. Estimated costs of interpreter-related delays are derived from HMCTS adjournment cost modelling (average cost per adjourned hearing multiplied by interpreter-attributed adjournments). Wrong-language booking figures from MOJ freedom of information responses and contractor reporting.",
    "knownIssues": [
      "Outsourcing contract transferred from Capita to thebigword in 2016 — data collection methods differ across contract periods.",
      "COVID-19 reduced court sittings in 2020, artificially lowering complaint and failure counts for that year.",
      "Remote video interpreting data only consistently recorded from 2021 onwards.",
      "Estimated cost figures are modelled, not directly measured — based on average adjournment costs applied to interpreter-attributed delays.",
      "Wrong-language booking counts rely partly on self-reporting by defendants and solicitors and are likely undercounted."
    ]
  }
